This article is a letter from President Barack Obama to the Speaker of the House of Representatives and the President of the Senate regarding the Disaster Relief Appropriations Act of 2013. The President designates all funding designated by Congress in the Act as emergency requirements, in accordance with section 902 of the Act. The President references section 251(b)(2)(A)(i) of the Balanced Budget and Emergency Deficit Control Act of 1985, as amended. The details of this action are outlined in an enclosed letter from the Deputy Director for Management of the Office of Management and Budget.